<h1 class="title">Anti-racism work begins with self-education</h1>
<div class="subTitle">The Office of the Vice-President, Equity and Community Inclusion offers educational resources to increase your racial literacy</div>

<div class="author">By: Antoinette Mercurio</div>
<div class="date">June 12, 2020</div>


</div>

	<div class="content stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resImageText section">


























		<div class="row" id="ad659b8d-56f3-4e69-8c32-df0dece9b8fa">
			<div class="col-xs-12">
				<div class="thumbnail customStyle1">
					
<img src="/content/dam/news-events/news/2020/06/eci-resources.jpg" alt="A hand holding open a book with other books around it, laid out on a table"/>




					 
						<div class="caption richtextContent">
	<p>Examining our own unconscious bias and self-study are the first steps in doing anti-racism work. Photo by <a href="https://www.pexels.com/@readymade?utm_content=attributionCopyText&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=pexels">ready made<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a> from <a href="https://www.pexels.com/photo/anonymous-crop-person-reading-book-on-marble-surface-with-other-books-3847614/?utm_content=attributionCopyText&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=pexels">Pexels<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a>.</p>
</div>
						    
					
